
`emerge` is primarily used for installing Portage-packages

code {
emerge [options] [action] [ebuild | tbz2file | file | @set | atom] ...
emerge --sync [repo | alias] ...
emerge --info [atom]
emerge --search somestring
emerge --help | --version
code }


{ TODO

  { --sync

   `emerge --sync` is a deprecated(?) command.

    In order to synchronize → Linux/distributions/Gentoo#ebuild-repo[ebuild repositories], `emaint` with the corresponding option should be used.

  }
  { --oneshot

    Using `emerge --oneshot` avoids adding a package to the world file (`→ Linux/fhs/var/lib/portage/world`).

  }

}
